"From URL: beautiful-soup-4.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\nSummary:\n    Beautiful Soup is a Python library designed for extracting data from HTML and XML documents, offering intuitive methods for navigating, searching, and modifying the parse tree. This comprehensive documentation covers its installation, core object types like Tag and NavigableString, and extensive functionalities for traversing the document structure both up and down. It details powerful search capabilities using various filters, regular expressions, and CSS selectors, alongside methods for modifying the tree and handling diverse output formats and character encodings.\n\nKeywords: Python library, HTML parsing, XML parsing, Web scraping, Parse tree, Tag, find_all, CSS selectors\nReferences: beautiful-soup-4.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\n"